OASISFormat: 0.3
Name: ucutf
Version: 0.9.0
Synopsis: Non-blocking streaming Unicode codec for OCaml
Authors: Daniel Bünzli <daniel.buenzli at erratique.ch>
Copyrights: (c) 2012 Daniel C. Bünzli
License: BSD3
Homepage: http://erratique.ch/software/ucutf
Description:
 UCutf is an OCaml module to encode and decode the UTF-{8,16,16LE,16BE} 
 encoding schemes. New line normalization and character position tracking 
 can be automatically performed on decoding.
 .
 Functions are also provided to fold over the characters of UTF encoded
 OCaml string values and to directly encode characters in OCaml Buffer.t
 values.
 .
 UCutf is made of a single, independent, module and distributed under
 the BSD3 license.

